Name: peripheral nervous system benign neoplasm
Definition: A T cell deficiency that is characterized by CD4 lymphopenia

Name: gangliocytoma
Definition: A central nervous system benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in mature neurons

Name: dysembryoplastic neuroepithelial tumor
Definition: A mixed neoplasm that is seen mostly in early infancy and that consists of classic and cellular (atypical) variants.

Name: craniopharyngioma
Definition: A pituitary gland benign neoplasm that derives_from glandular epithelial cells.

Name: benign meningioma
Definition: A Chromadorea infectious disease that involves infection of humans and domestic animals by parasitic roundworms with three lips on the anteriour end.

Name: ganglioglioma
Definition: A cell type benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in glial-type cells.
